  description="Pool excavation in Berwick — planning permits, building permits, neighbour notification, easement checks, soil-haul volumes, and the 8-ton vs mini-excavator choice. SPASA Victoria member."
  canonical="https://berwickpools.com.au/pool-excavation-berwick/">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">The week the project becomes real</span>
      <h1>Pool excavation in Berwick — <span class="accent">what Council needs, what neighbours need, and how the dig actually works</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Excavation is the visible turning point of every pool build. This page walks
        through the City of Casey pre-build process, the easement and overlay
        checks, the soil-haul calculation for reactive Casey clay, and the
        excavator decision that drives a third of the build cost.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a site visit</a>
      </div>
    </div>
